<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-10736] TestTopology.simple_decommission_test failing due to assertion triggered by SizeEstimatesRecorder</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-10736</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Example &lt;a href=&quot;http://cassci.datastax.com/job/cassandra-2.2_dtest/369/testReport/junit/topology_test/TestTopology/simple_decommission_test/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;SizeEstimatesRecorder&lt;/tt&gt; can race with decommission when it tries to get the primary ranges for a node.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is because &lt;tt&gt;getPredecessor&lt;/tt&gt; in &lt;tt&gt;TokenMetadata&lt;/tt&gt; hits an assertion if the token is no longer in &lt;tt&gt;TokenMetadata&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This no longer occurs in 3.0 because this assertion has been removed and replace with different data.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In both cases, the relationship between the set of tokens in &lt;tt&gt;getPrimaryRangesFor&lt;/tt&gt; (passed in as an argument) and the set of tokens used in calls by &lt;tt&gt;getPredecessor&lt;/tt&gt; (the system ones) should be investigated.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
