                            <comment id="15121865" author="jkni" created="Thu, 28 Jan 2016 16:48:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have patches for this and just need to verify if the changes in behavior to &lt;tt&gt;getPredecessor&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;getSuccessor&lt;/tt&gt; are necessary.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=blambov&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;blambov&quot;&gt;blambov&lt;/a&gt; It looks like these changes went in as part of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-7032&quot; title=&quot;Improve vnode allocation&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-7032&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-7032&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. Prior to this, in &lt;tt&gt;TokenMetadata&lt;/tt&gt;, &lt;tt&gt;getPredecessor&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;getSuccessor&lt;/tt&gt; threw errors if tokens weren&apos;t in the endpoint map. After &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-7032&quot; title=&quot;Improve vnode allocation&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-7032&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-7032&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, the first token is selected. Is this an intended change? Tests continue to pass with this reverted.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15121894" author="blambov" created="Thu, 28 Jan 2016 17:03:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t believe these changes are necessary. I think I used them for tests but didn&apos;t really intend to keep the change.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
